HEADWORD: Zoophorous
<hw>Zo*oph"o*rous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr. Gr.
<?/. See <er>Zoophoric</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Anc. Arch.)</fld> <def>The
part between the architrave and cornice; the frieze; -- so called from
the figures of animals carved upon it.</def>⟦br⟧
